# Significant Changes Summary

> **Purpose:** Distilled record of meaningful changes — architecture decisions, new features, breaking changes, and resolved issues. This is the high-level story of the project's evolution.

## Instructions

- One entry per **meaningful milestone**: new feature, bug fix, refactor, config change, dependency update, or decision.
- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD | <type> | <scope> | <summary>`
- Focus on **what changed and why**, not every keystroke (that's what `each-step-log.mdc` is for).
- Mark breaking changes with `[BREAKING]` prefix.
- Link to the relevant commit hash when available.

## Type Legend

| Type | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `FEAT` | New feature or capability |
| `FIX` | Bug fix |
| `REFACTOR` | Code restructuring, no behavior change |
| `CONFIG` | Configuration change |
| `DEPS` | Dependency update |
| `DOCS` | Documentation |
| `PERF` | Performance improvement |
| `BREAKING` | Backward-incompatible change (prefix) |
| `OPS` | Operational / deployment / CI change |

